          {
            "possibleIdentity": "Peter Deal was a British photographer and artist active in New York City during the late 1960s and early 1970s. He trained under photography legends Irving Penn and Bert Stern and worked on Stern's famous \"The Last Sitting\" series with Marilyn Monroe. Known for his technical mastery as a black-and-white printer and a \"fashion and beauty perfectionist,\" his work placed him within the same professional circles as those involved with Experiments in Art and Technology (E.A.T.). In historical documentation and multimedia archives of E.A.T. projects (such as \"9 Evenings: Theatre and Engineering\"), photo credits and captions sometimes reference a \"DEAL photo,\" suggesting his role in documenting or collaborating with the organization's founders, Billy Klüver and Robert Rauschenberg.",
